claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Forest plot showing relative vaccine effectiveness (with 95% CIs) of a recombinant influenza vaccine versus a standard-dose influenza vaccine among participants aged 50–64, stratified by preexisting conditions and outcomes (PCR-confirmed influenza, hospitalization for PCR-confirmed influenza, and hospitalization for community-acquired pneumonia). The figure presents subgroup analyses of relative vaccine effectiveness, but it does not provide any data on hemagglutinin antigen content or its comparison (e.g., 3× HA) between Flublok and standard-dose vaccines, and thus does not support the claim. Note: The image is clear regarding effectiveness outcomes but contains no information on antigen content or immunogenicity differences related to HA quantity.
